# aisoc.config.example — single-file configuration for the AISOC demo
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. Copy this file to `aisoc.config` (gitignored) at the repo root.
# 2. Uncomment + fill in the values you want to override.
# 3. Run ./aisoc_demo.sh deploy — the script sources this file before
#    parsing CLI flags, so:
#      - aisoc.config            sets the baseline
#      - --flag=value on CLI     overrides aisoc.config for that run
#      - pre-set env in shell    overrides everything
#
# This is bash-`source`d, so use shell syntax (no quotes needed for
# simple values; quote anything containing spaces, JSON, or special
# characters).
#
# Most values map to Terraform variables via the TF_VAR_<name> contract
# Terraform supports natively. A few are deploy-script-level (no
# TF_VAR_ prefix). Both kinds are listed below.

# ── Azure subscription / resource group / region ────────────────────
# Resource group Phase 1 will create (if it doesn't exist) and Phases
# 2 + 3 will deploy into.
# TF_VAR_resource_group_name="rg-aisoc-demo"

# Region for Phase 1 (Sentinel + lab VM).
# TF_VAR_azure_location="westus"

# Region for Phase 2 (Function Apps). EP-series quota is most readily
# available in westcentralus on freshly-onboarded subscriptions.
# TF_VAR_location_override="westcentralus"

# Region for Foundry. Model Router + gpt-4.1-mini are gated to
# eastus2 / swedencentral.
# TF_VAR_foundry_location="eastus2"

# Override the active Azure subscription before any deploy step runs
# (defaults to whatever `az account show` returns).
# AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_OVERRIDE="6e961575-c100-444e-a868-1972223b2410"

# ── Lab VM ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Lab VM admin password. If left unset, Phase 1 generates a random
# 28-char password (held in Terraform state, stable across re-applies)
# and the deploy script prints it at the end. Set explicitly here if
# you need a specific password.
# TF_VAR_admin_password="<your-vm-password>"

# Override the default admin username.
# TF_VAR_admin_username="azureadmin"

# VM size. Default is Standard_D2s_v3.
# TF_VAR_vm_size="Standard_D2s_v3"

# ── Foundry model deployment ────────────────────────────────────────
# Model identity. Defaults match the validated demo combo.
# TF_VAR_foundry_model_choice="gpt-4.1-mini"
# TF_VAR_foundry_model_version="2025-04-14"
# TF_VAR_foundry_model_deployment_name="gpt-4.1-mini"

# SKU + capacity. Capacity is in **thousands of TPM** for the
# GlobalStandard SKU — 1500 = 1,500,000 TPM.
# TF_VAR_foundry_model_sku_name="GlobalStandard"
# TF_VAR_foundry_model_sku_capacity="1500"

# ── Demo login roster (PixelAgents Web) ─────────────────────────────
# JSON object: {email: password}. Wired into the Container App as a
# secret (encrypted at rest), exposed to the server as
# AISOC_USERS_JSON. Adding/removing users from the demo is a one-
# line edit to this file + `terraform apply` in Phase 3.
#
# Demo-grade only: passwords are stored verbatim. Don't reuse real
# credentials here.
#
# Pure single-line JSON keeps the bash escaping simple — no nested
# quotes inside the string.
# TF_VAR_pixelagents_users='{"erik.vanbuggenhout@nviso.eu":"admin123","jeroen.laureys@nviso.eu":"saleswarmachine"}'

# ── OpenRouter (optional) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Only needed if you've wired the gateway to call OpenRouter as well
# as Foundry — leave commented for the standard demo.
# TF_VAR_openrouter_api_key="sk-or-v1-..."

# ── Deploy-script-level options ─────────────────────────────────────
# Skip the OIDC bootstrap step on subsequent runs (the one-time SP +
# federated-credential setup). Useful in CI loops where the trust is
# already configured.
# AISOC_SKIP_OIDC=1

# GitHub repo to sync repo-vars into. Defaults to ErikVabu-Personal/
# aisoc-lab; override here if you fork.
# AISOC_GITHUB_REPO="<owner>/<repo>"
